post_text: Howdy there...I need to let y'all know that I had to go ahead and make the decision to postpone the trip till next year. Mr Hartgraves is happy to let us go next year. The travel agent said he will apply money paid to next year, and he will work to keep the cost as close as possible to the same. Disney parks are closed "until further notice" and when they do open, it will be a phasing in situation over a couple months where not all parks will be open, and not running at full capacity. This years seniors are invited to return and travel with us. And we will work on earning the money for the 10-12 new 8th graders. It's very sad, but maybe when this virus mess is all over we can look at a couple options to make the trip even better next year. I will post a statement on the google classroom page.

post_text:
***Notice to all band parents and members of proposed amendment to the current Senior scholarship bi-law**

-The vote for the proposal will be April 1st at the monthly band booster meeting.

-Current bi-law for the scholarship is every current Senior in band in good standings and having applied and been accepted to college will receive $50.00 per year of active band participation (ex: in band 4 years would receive $200.00)

-New proposal will give one Senior male and one Senior female a $250.00 scholarship. They will be required to submit an essay and all essays will be judged anonymously by a professor at Tarleton. If proposal is approved the Seniors will be given the essay requirements and a deadline to have them turned in Mr Wright by.

All band parents are welcome to vote April 1st on the proposed change.

post_text:
Good morning my peeps
We will have a bake sale down at the Billy the Kid festival Saturday April 1st. We are asking for all our wonderful bakers to come forward with all kinds of goodies. The more we have the more money we can raise. Our goal is a 20 foot trailer to haul equipment uniforms and instrument as the band has out grown the old trailer. So all the help we can get is welcomed. You can drop off at the booth saturday morning. I wont know which space we will be in until saturday. But i will posted asap.

As always thank you for everything you do.

Gayla Gauss
BB President
